About
LISBON ZOO ‚Äì GO AROUND THE WORLD IN JUST ONE DAY At Lisbon Zoo, we invite you to travel around the world without leaving Lisbon. Find the Sumatran Tigers in the dense vegetation of the Rainforest, observe Lions, Giraffes and Elephants behaviour at the dry African Savannah and dazzle with the majestic flight of the colourful birds of South America. Our mission is to develop and promote a zoological and botanical park, as a centre of conservation, reproduction and reintroduction of endangered species, through scientific investigation and environmental enrichment programs. Along with education is a strong entertainment component that will ensure a great family time, always with the conviction that when visiting Lisbon Zoo you‚Äôre contributing to this great project of conservations of endangered species and their habitats.
Duration: More than 3 hours
Does not meet animal welfare guidelines
Tripadvisor does not provide bookings for this experience because it does not meet our animal welfare guidelines.

    Brilliant zoo - dolphin show, bears, tigers, etc
    Amazing zoo, we had such a lovely day. Visited with two children aged 7 and 10 and they both loved it. We travelled there from our hotel via metro, which was really easy and the stop is directly outside the zoo. We didn't buy our tickets in advance and it was easy to buy the tickets when we got to the zoo using a machine. Queue was short to get in. They stamp your hand with a UV stamp so you can leave and re-enter, but it comes off easily, so beware. My daughters came off, but they didn't question it as obviously she was with us and we all had stamps. Lots of animals to see and the chair lifts are amazing for fab views of the city and animals. Train was good and not expensive (this was the only attraction you had to pay extra for on top of your tickets). Chair lift was free. McDonalds and Lidl right next to the zoo. Dolphin show was great, we watched it twice. Would really recommend for a great day out.

Worldwide Traveller
London, UK151 contributions
Children will love it!
Jun 2024 ‚Ä¢ Family
The zoo is located towards the North part of the city but it's very easily accesable using the tube's blue line, just 5 minutes from the Marques de Pombal station.

You can buy your ticket in advance, using machines located at the entrance or with the staff there. Staff will hand you a map upon entering the zoo, we'd encourage you to start by going to the right hand side, working your way up, then down the centre and then down on the left hand side so you end up by the dolphinarium.

This is a perfect place to spend a solid 5 hours with little children, they'll love the opportunity to roam free, see many species of animals (from elephants to snakes to birds, you name it). There are many shaded places to sit and take a break, some of them are just lovely with walls covered in classical Portuguese tiles).

There are a few places to get some food and icecream for a decent price, just be patient with the staff manning these locales, time has got a different meaning to them. Also worth mentioning there are a number of free wc areas scattered across the zoo.

Tip: ensure your mobile phone is fully charged as you will surely be taking many pictures of your children having the time of their lifes. Those are memories you'll cherish for years to come.
Written June 30, 2024
